  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Preschool English Assistant Teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<p><br>\nWe welcome individuals who are passionate about working with young children and eager to start their career in early childhood education. As an Assistant Preschool Teacher, you will:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Support the main teacher in daily lessons and classroom activities.</li>\n  <li>Prepare learning materials and assist with setting up engaging activity corners.</li>\n  <li>Participate in interactive activities such as songs, games, and storytelling.</li>\n  <li>Help observe and record children’s progress under the guidance of the main teacher.</li>\n  <li>Maintain a clean, safe, and child-friendly environment.</li>\n  <li>Assist in supervising children during indoor and outdoor play.</li>\n  <li>Build positive relationships with children, parents, and colleagues.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Certificate/Diploma in Early Childhood Care &amp; Education, or currently pursuing related studies (students awaiting graduation are welcome).</li>\n  <li>Friendly, caring, and approachable personality.</li>\n  <li>Willingness to learn and take guidance from senior educators.</li>\n  <li>Enjoys working in a team and supporting others.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
